methods.initialize:
Initialize this operation.

:param usePrev: (boolean) - data from the previous cycle should be used (otherwise use this cycle)
:param beforeClock: (long) - the clock value that we captured before the function began; the function can use this
        value to bail out early if it notices something has gone wrong.
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.QueryTable.Operation.Result<io.deephaven.engine.v2.QueryTable>) the result table / listener if successful, null if it should be retried.
methods.transform:

*Overload 1*  
  :param rowSetToTransform: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.RowSet) - the outer rowSet

methods.transformPrev:
Transform an outer (reversed) rowSet to the inner (unreversed) rowSet as of the previous cycle, or vice versa.

*Overload 1*  
  :param outerRowSet: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.RowSet) - the outer rowSet
